        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 3:47PM EDT by NWS Gray ME</headline>
        <description>At 347 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorms
over Rindge, or near Jaffrey, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rindge, New Boston, New Ipswich, Sharon, Goffstown, Jaffrey, Mount
Vernon, Lyndeborough, Merrimack, Mont Vernon, Milford, Greenville,
Litchfield, Wilton, Greenfield, Brookline, Peterborough, Mason,
Temple, and Amherst.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
southern and central New Hampshire.</instruction>
